{
  "texts": [
    "Due to the input constraints of LLMs, models like ChatGPT can support a maximum of 4096 tokens in a single call, including both input and output.",
    "In multi-turn dialogue scenarios, longer dialogue contexts often meet the risk of exceeding this token limit.",
    "The simplest approach to tackle this challenge is to trim the dialogue by discarding earlier turns.",
    "However, in conversational recommender systems, users may express a significant amount of personal information and interests in the early stages of the conversation.",
    "The omission of such information directly impacts the accuracy of recommendations."
  ]
}